I recognize the behavior since installing callisto a few weeks ago (kept uptodate). After disabling all callisto plugins and a restart, I can start the other eclipse instance. But when callisto is enabled again, after an (arbitrary) times of successful starting the other eclipse instance, it crashes again. 

I do not need do disable all callisto plugins. Disabling e.g. TPTP or BIRT works too. But the success is not permanent. It seems to me that eclipse simply needs a change in the plugin configuration.

As far as I remember, the problem never occurs when callisto is completly disabled.
